\title{Closed-Loop BCI: FUS Stimulation + EEG Recording}
\taxon{design}
\author{barton-rhodes}
\date{2026-04-08}
\import{macros}
\tag{fus}
\tag{eeg}
\tag{closed-loop}
\tag{neurofeedback}
\tag{gf3}
\meta{modality}{neurostimulation+electrophysiological}
\meta{scope}{bci-factory}

\p{Status: closed-loop design direction combining aspirational FUS stimulation with high-channel EEG references. Validate against actual loaned hardware and safety review before implementation claims.}

\p{Closed-loop architecture connecting focused ultrasound stimulation (\ref{bcf-0056}) with EEG recording (\ref{bcf-0052}, \ref{bcf-0053}). The HD-72 64ch EEG reads cortical evoked responses; the Rigol AWG + 300kHz transducer writes to the same cortical targets. The loop closes through the processing pipeline, creating a read-write brain-computer interface.}

\subtree{\title{Read-Write Channel Pairing}
\taxon{design}

\table{
\tr{\th{Cortex}\th{FUS target}\th{EEG channels (10-20)}\th{Signal}\th{Latency}}
\tr{\td{S1 (touch)}\td{Somatosensory}\td{C3, C4, CP3, CP4}\td{Somatosensory evoked potential (SEP)}\td{20-50ms}}
\tr{\td{V1 (sight)}\td{Visual}\td{O1, O2, Oz, POz}\td{Visual evoked potential (VEP)}\td{75-150ms}}
\tr{\td{A1 (hearing)}\td{Auditory}\td{T7, T8, C5, C6}\td{Auditory evoked potential (AEP)}\td{10-100ms}}
\tr{\td{OlfBulb (smell)}\td{Olfactory bulb}\td{Fp1, Fp2, AF3, AF4}\td{Olfactory evoked potential (OEP)}\td{200-500ms}}
}

\p{The HD-72 (\ref{bcf-0052}) covers all four targets simultaneously with its 64-channel montage. FUS stimulates one target at a time (sequential beam steering). The EEG confirms whether the stimulation produced the expected evoked potential.}
}

\subtree{\title{Closed-Loop Pipeline}
\taxon{design}

\pre{\startverb
FUS transducer (300kHz)          HD-72 64ch EEG
    |                                |
    v                                v
Rigol AWG waveform           Delta decoder (bcf-0053)
    |                                |
    v                                v
Cortical target              64ch -> LSL stream
    |                                |
    +------ skull + cortex ----------+
    |        (the brain)             |
    v                                v
Evoked response              nk.erp_process()
                                     |
                                     v
                             Evoked potential detected?
                                     |
                            +--------+--------+
                            |                 |
                         YES (trit +1)     NO (trit -1)
                            |                 |
                            v                 v
                    Adjust: amplitude    Adjust: beam angle
                    or target next       or increase power
                    cortical region      within safety limits
                            |                 |
                            +--------+--------+
                                     |
                                     v
                              Next FUS pulse
                              (closed loop)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{\title{GF(3) Trit Classification of Stimulation Response}
\taxon{definition}

\table{
\tr{\th{Response}\th{Trit}\th{EEG signature}\th{Action}}
\tr{\td{Evoked}\td{+1}\td{Significant ERP in target channels, p < 0.05 vs baseline}\td{Stimulation effective. Log and proceed.}}
\tr{\td{Ambiguous}\td{0}\td{Weak ERP, near noise floor}\td{Increase power or adjust coupling. Retry.}}
\tr{\td{No response}\td{-1}\td{No ERP above baseline}\td{Reposition transducer. Check coupling gel. Verify target coordinates.}}
}

\p{The trit feeds back into beam steering decisions. This is the same GF(3) classification used for HRV in vibesnipe (\ref{bci-0018}) -- the autonomic trit and the cortical trit are independent channels that can be combined in the goblin swarm coplay.}
}

\subtree{\title{Safety Constraints}
\taxon{remark}

\ul{
\li{\strong{ISPTA limit}: spatial-peak temporal-average intensity below 720 mW/cm2 (FDA diagnostic ultrasound limit)}
\li{\strong{Duty cycle}: pulsed mode only, never continuous wave for stimulation}
\li{\strong{Session duration}: max 30 minutes per cortical target per day}
\li{\strong{EEG watchdog}: if afterdischarge detected (sustained high-amplitude oscillation post-stimulus), immediately halt FUS and alert operator}
\li{\strong{No olfactory FUS without IRB}: only 2 studies exist (Chizhov). S1 and A1 are the safe starting targets.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{Integration with Vivarium Network}
\taxon{remark}

\p{The FUS rig and HD-72 sit on VLAN 10 (Trusted) in the alterstructure (\ref{bcf-0055}). The closed-loop pipeline runs on the DGX (\ref{bcf-0057} inventory). LSL multicast carries both EEG streams and FUS trigger signals within VLAN 10.}

\p{Data flow: HD-72 serial (3 Mbaud, FTDI) -> workstation -> LSL -> DGX -> NeuroKit2 ERP detection -> FUS control signal -> Rigol AWG (SCPI over ethernet or USB-TMC).}
}

\subtree{\title{Connections}
\taxon{remark}

\ul{
\li{\ref{bcf-0056} -- FUS hardware: Rigol AWG + 300kHz transducer + tongue electrodes}
\li{\ref{bcf-0052} -- HD-72 64ch EEG pipeline design}
